      "relations": null,
      "text": [
        " أَفْضَلُ الصَّدَقَةِ إِبْرَادُ كَبِدٍ حَرَّى ."
      ],
      "translations": {
        "en.hubeali": [
          "Muhammad, from Abdullah Bin Muhammad, from Ali Bin Al Hakam, from Aban Bin Usman, from Misma’a, ",
          "(It has been narrated) from Abu Abdullah<sup>asws</sup> having said: ‘The most superior of the charities is cooling the hot liver (quenching ones thirst)’."
        ],
        "en.sarwar": [
          "2. Muhammad has narrated from ‘Abd Allah ibn Muhammad from Ali ibn al-Hakam from Aban ibn ‘Uthman from Misma’ who has said the following: “Abu ‘Abd Allah, ‘Alayhi al-Salam, has said that the best charity is cooling off a thirsty liver.” "
        ]
      }
